resistencia","guid":"eVF19hmdTsmjUYmkmOwygw","children":[]}]},{"id":"131","parent":"118","text":"AFBN → ATB PROLONGADO 3-4 SEMANAS","guid":"MZZQmzK6ROSdPLQ21bKFVw","children":[{"id":"132","parent":"131","text":"2 semanas → riesgo de recaida o infeccion persistente","guid":"2EDmnJ-3T_ei5zysG89aPA","children":[]},{"id":"133","parent":"131","text":"Inicio IV → switch oral segun respuesta","guid":"1hF6-AaKTimgNw7IsJw9KA","children":[]}]},{"id":"134","parent":"118","text":"Enfisematosa → ATB amplio espectro + CONTROL DE FOCO","guid":"OyD8ykObRJqC12d-VYf9wA","children":[]}]},{"id":"135","parent":"114","text":"Soporte","guid":"hp3hwSSHQDWAIpyTPfle8Q","children":[{"id":"136","parent":"135","text":"Resucitacion con fluidos","guid":"6TlUFDrkTf6SYuUom5JvYA","children":[{"id":"137","parent":"136","text":"Sepsis: 30 mL/kg cristaloide isotonico en 3h","guid":"mpIEZBjZSuSEUSdDTtlqtQ","children":[]}]},{"id":"138","parent":"135","text":"Analgesicos, antipireticos, antiemeticos","guid":"84maNlTiRBSNGHENShhTjw","children":[]}]},{"id":"139","parent":"114","text":"Control de foco (CRITICO en complicadas)","guid":"bc54H8Q8ReO7OFPK29vBag","children":[{"id":"140","parent":"139","text":"Hidronefrosis obstructiva → drenaje URGENTE","guid":"OxPVs4ASSDi__6MZZUDX3g","children":[{"id":"141","parent":"140","text":"Cateter ureteral (doble J) o nefrostomia percutanea","guid":"JmrIshSKThGqNjeHwfYJ2w","children":[]}]},{"id":"142","parent":"139","text":"Absceso renal >5 cm o paciente inestable → drenaje percutaneo","guid":"Z6eWDw_LSze8vEQTl-cFRw","children":[]},{"id":"143","parent":"139","text":"Absceso <3-5 cm → puede resolver con ATB solos","guid":"PmQ2BILqRB-cChl5NUfiIA","children":[]},{"id":"144","parent":"139","text":"Enfisematosa → nefrectomia si inestabilidad refractaria","guid":"zt3zTcbOQXePCjfedNzrRw","children":[{"id":"145","parent":"144","text":"Mejor outcome con manejo medico + quirurgico vs solo medico","guid":"RYgLjcKcTHmLkTzeWnsojg","children":[]}]},{"id":"146","parent":"139","text":"Pionefrosis → drenaje INMEDIATO","guid":"ICd2laiWQlOXak2zBZCOmA","children":[]}]},{"id":"147","parent":"114","text":"Monitorizacion","guid":"1BBrn0BdSKm8gm_2X5dCfA","children":[{"id":"148","parent":"147","text":"Sin mejoria 24-48h → repetir urocultivo + imagenes","guid":"LCiyhnxnQTO_e271dkysCw","children":[]},{"id":"149","parent":"147","text":"Seguimiento cercano si alta con oral antes de antibiograma","guid":"-q4cwBKMRYCKHSHYJJdrdQ","children":[]},{"id":"150","parent":"147","text":"Control imagenologico en AFBN para documentar resolucion","guid":"9SPiJAc9QBevVxZOOcpJFw","children":[]}]},{"id":"151","parent":"114","text":"Duracion ATB","guid":"9PQcpweZTle7Ky45ipySgw","children":[{"id":"152","parent":"151","text":"Fluoroquinolona: 5-7 dias (PNA no complicada)","guid":"6DgqmqMlRk6KppohGmti1g","children":[]},{"id":"153","parent":"151","text":"TMP-SMX: 14 dias","guid":"sNAKXqonTqCLvlUfYN7YsQ","children":[]},{"id":"154","parent":"151","text":"AFBN: 3-4 semanas minimo","guid":"GOOvxAAZQiyXp7GBjLAIEg","children":[]},{"id":"155","parent":"151","text":"Absceso drenado: 2-4 semanas segun evolucion","guid":"3n5vyShRT-KAOSazRzh81g","children":[]},{"id":"156","parent":"151","text":"Enfisematosa: curso prolongado individualizado","guid":"SCEhLkBaSJ-zfYmIH130jA","children":[]}]}]},{"id":"157","parent":"0","text":"Consideraciones Geriatricas","guid":"mgro2PsETrOGnZ3oDmAroQ","children":[{"id":"158","parent":"157","text":"Mayor riesgo de complicaciones y mortalidad","guid":"770PIJQqSFCEdxFHzIGi2Q","children":[]},{"id":"159","parent":"157","text":"Presentacion atipica → delirium, deterioro funcional, caidas","guid":"G1sTQ_baSdOq3wvy3VopBQ","children":[]},{"id":"160","parent":"157","text":"Bacteriemia mas frecuente en >65 anos","guid":"5RXaNimhRqOuAhC_zD7bew","children":[]},{"id":"161","parent":"157","text":"E. coli menos predominante (~60%) → mas variedad microbiologica","guid":"6N9-5MNlTfqcfZt3HW6rnQ","children":[]},{"id":"162","parent":"157","text":"Mayor prevalencia de MDR por hospitalizaciones y cateterizaciones previas","guid":"OKmKO-8OTOeG_Yf1uXx4mA","children":[]},{"id":"163","parent":"157","text":"Ajustar ATB por TFG (CKD-EPI) → EVITAR nefrotoxicos si posible","guid":"DkmzzoeURmm9bxUIh4NLsw","children":[]},{"id":"164","parent":"157","text":"Aminoglucosidos → monitorizar niveles, nefro/ototoxicidad","guid":"UnqrQppMTTeqT_dNZY4bEA","children":[]},{"id":"165","parent":"157","text":"Fluoroquinolonas → riesgo tendininopatia, prolongacion QTc, delirium","guid":"m1QLjOq9TGWLhl-Y_AccpQ","children":[]},{"id":"166","parent":"157","text":"Interacciones farmacologicas por POLIFARMACIA","guid":"W-6KVHYVTsigRg_ymTB0VQ","children":[]},{"id":"167","parent":"157","text":"Resucitacion con fluidos → CUIDADO con sobrecarga en IC/ERC","guid":"a-rBTCZLSaS9p_V9XHq8tg","children":[]},{"id":"168","parent":"157","text":"Funcionalidad basal (Barthel/Lawton) como predictor de outcomes","guid":"lSUhkXYbRjSs6MaYlEaFJg","children":[]},{"id":"169","parent":"157","text":"Proporcionalidad terapeutica → considerar CFS, voluntades anticipadas","guid":"VXQ_BsugTae14C264IUTuw","children":[]}]},{"id":"170","parent":"0","text":"Perlas Clinicas","guid":"wv7XqF4yR32PQAGMDJG5Mg","children":[{"id":"171","parent":"170","text":"Fiebre persistente >=4 dias con ATB adecuado → sospechar AFBN/absceso → TC con contraste","guid":"-o7xdw6UTxa344ivEKRi6g","children":[]},{"id":"172","parent":"170","text":"AFBN es clinicamente IDENTICA a PNA → solo se diferencia por imagen","guid":"x2CXJARjSXKK3mPb4-OTJA","children":[]},{"id":"173","parent":"170","text":"TC con contraste = GOLD STANDARD para complicaciones de PNA","guid":"4Oa8XFcER6-3hPtZm4s29A","children":[]},{"id":"174","parent":"170","text":"Ecografia NORMAL no descarta patologia renal significativa","guid":"8D-Y34CdQVawL-99n0dYXg","children":[]},{"id":"175","parent":"170","text":"Enfisematosa → mortalidad 38% → buscar gas en TC sin contraste en diabeticos","guid":"nHrxIEGJTGy9XLZRH1ZQ-g","children":[]},{"id":"176","parent":"170","text":"Pionefrosis = emergencia urologica → drenaje antes que ATB solos","guid":"Wyd1qkEFRbuEsQ3zhcliyQ","children":[]},{"id":"177","parent":"170","text":"AFBN requiere 3-4 semanas de ATB → 2 semanas = recaida","guid":"BN37kNScTuCXeXgrAeBUEg","children":[]},{"id":"178","parent":"170","text":"En adulto mayor con delirium + leucocitosis → descartar PNA complicada aunque no haya dolor lumbar","guid":"612jcMNaROO-6S45YVNmOQ","children":[]},{"id":"179","parent":"170","text":"Urocultivo negativo NO descarta AFBN ni absceso","guid":"pPBQXKShQgGTB8d8mhtH_g","children":[]},{"id":"180","parent":"170","text":"Xantogranulomatosa puede simular cancer renal → histologia es diagnostica","guid":"WwfcWoFrRxKso-qJYL3B5w","children":[]},{"id":"181","parent":"170","text":"Start low, go slow con ATB en AM pero alcanzar dosis terapeuticas","guid":"idYpmvYOQdmLVi9j5Hc9rA","children":[]}]},{"id":"182","parent":"0","text":"Referencias","guid":"YAZ6gHD7SQ2-9DRlMVuruQ","children":[]},{"id":"183","parent":"0","text":"1. Rosenfield AT et al. Acute focal bacterial nephritis (acute lobar nephronia). Radiology. 1979;132:553-61.","guid":"KlwGKB_7SEWBUY8lkz3oMg","children":[]},{"id":"184","parent":"0","text":"2. Johnson JR, Russo TA. Acute Pyelonephritis in Adults. N Engl J Med. 2018;378(1):48-59.","guid":"SjLuV_GBT9G5hKH58GnHiQ","children":[]},{"id":"185","parent":"0","text":"3. Devlin JW et al. CPG for Pain, Agitation/Sedation, Delirium. Crit Care Med. 2018;46(9):e825-e873.","guid":"lXDEMDi-R9q4kI_lvIqhLg","children":[]},{"id":"186","parent":"0","text":"4. Cheng CH et al. Is acute lobar nephronia the midpoint in the spectrum of upper UTIs? J Pediatr. 2010;156:82-86.","guid":"nVwdArozROiTAcq8f96xXA","children":[]},{"id":"187","parent":"0","text":"5. Huang JJ, Tseng CC. Emphysematous pyelonephritis: clinicoradiological classification. Am J Med. 2000;109(1):7-12.","guid":"qKKDmGNbQgSyORSbjaYgVg","children":[]},{"id":"188","parent":"0","text":"6. Gupta K et al. International CPG for treatment of acute uncomplicated cystitis and pyelonephritis. Clin Infect Dis. 2011;52(5):e103-e120.","guid":"QLG4HDmESdOBvgd1H6KcKA","children":[]},{"id":"189","parent":"0","text":"7. EAU Guidelines on Urological Infections. Eur Urol. 2024;86(1):16-35.","guid":"godVQiqyQmmpQh6LGMG5ig","children":[]},{"id":"190","parent":"0","text":"8. Sun J et al. Clinical features of AFBN in adults. Sci Rep. 2022;12(1):7404.","guid":"W5V-MSGYSlmtjCxv_lN1gQ","children":[]},{"id":"191","parent":"0","text":"9. StatPearls. Renal Abscess. NCBI Bookshelf. Updated Apr 2025.","guid":"AiauSZJGSk-VuzDpKHtxlg","children":[]},{"id":"192","parent":"0","text":"10. StatPearls. Acute Pyelonephritis. NCBI Bookshelf. Updated Feb 2024.","guid":"UWPAA_paQSWBWpctDjObzQ","children":[]},{"id":"193","parent":"0","text":"11. IDSA. CPG for complicated UTIs including pyelonephritis. 2024.","guid":"izwerBwBSjK0C0ViqYxMng","children":[]}]},"node_count":193,"relations":[],"cross_references":[],"specialty":"Infectología","folder":"Entidades clínicas/Infectología","filename":"Pielonefritis Flegmonosa","id":"map_1172","resolved_references":[],"title_raw":"Pielonefritis Flegmonosa"}